
	MVC in J2EE:
	============

	M - Model   
		(java)
		common format file	(Reuse)	
		java resources --> src folder --> sub package create
		(only setter and getter method - pojo class)
		(plain old java object)

		setter method : value assign (arg passing must)
		getter method : value return(don't pass arg)
			
		ex:
		public class classname
		{
			private datatype var;
			public returntype(datype or class (dont give void)) get()
			{
				return var;
			} 
			public void  set(datatype value)
			{
			var=value;
			}
		}
	rules:
		variable must be private.
		method must be public.
	advantages of using pojo class?

			*) memory management efficient
			*) do not modifiy pojo class members to others.
			
	V - View
		(html,jsp)
		output(result)
		webcontent --> folder create --> filename.html or filename.jsp
	C - Controller
		(servlet)
		business logic (for,while,......if,....)
		java resources --> src folder --> sub package create
		





